					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-789799#post-1986514</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-789799/scp-2019#post-1986514</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sat, 08 Mar 2014 07:33:05 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Dr Reach</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1779895</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Okay, I want to glomp this one. It runs away from the traditional reality-bender-who-is-all-powerful-and-relatable and makes a jello cube&#8230; adorable.</p> <p>Yeah, pretty much. +1</p> <p>However, there is a bit of a nitpick&#8230; brains? How do we know they are <em>brains</em>? Because they look like brains? I mean&#8230; they may <em>look</em> like brains, and we make the assumption that they <em>are</em> brains, but there is no actual way to confirm they are, functionally. It is an alien entity, after all, its physiology should be rather different from our own and even when we study those things, how do we know they don't perform some other vital function to 2019? Are they structurally similar at all to the human brain? Etcetera.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
